[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Succeeding the classic Visual Basic version 6.0, the first version of Visual Basic .NET debuted in 2002.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] As of 2020, ten versions of Visual Basic .NET are released.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] The first version, Visual Basic .NET, relies on .NET Framework 1.0.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] The most important feature is managed code, which contrasts with the classic Visual Basic.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic .NET 2003 was released with .NET Framework 1.1.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] New features included support for the .NET Compact Framework and a better VB upgrade wizard.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Improvements were also made to the performance and reliability of .NET IDE (particularly the background compiler) and runtime.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] In addition, Visual Basic .NET 2003 was available in the Visual Studio.NET Academic Edition, distributed to a certain number of scholars from each country without cost.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] After Visual Basic .NET 2003, Microsoft dropped ".NET" from the name of the product, calling the next version Visual Basic 2005.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic 2005 introduced the `IsNot` operator that makes `'If X IsNot Y'` equivalent to `'If Not X Is Y'`.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] It gained notoriety when it was found to be the subject of a Microsoft patent application.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic 9.0 was released along with .NET Framework 3.5 on November 19, 2007.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] In April 2010, Microsoft released Visual Basic 2010.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Microsoft had planned to use Dynamic Language Runtime (DLR) for that release but shifted to a co-evolution strategy between Visual Basic and sister language C# to bring both languages into closer parity with one another.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic's innate ability to interact dynamically with CLR and COM objects has been enhanced to work with dynamic languages built on the DLR such as IronPython and IronRuby.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] The Visual Basic compiler was improved to infer line continuation in a set of common contexts, in many cases removing the need for the " _" line continuation characters.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Also, existing support of inline Functions was complemented with support for inline Subs as well as multi-line versions of both Sub and Function lambdas.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic 2012 was released alongside .NET Framework 4.5.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic 2013 was released alongside .NET Framework 4.5.1 with Visual Studio 2013.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Can also build .NET Framework 4.5.2 applications by installing Developer Pack.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic 2015 (code named VB "14.0") was released with Visual Studio 2015.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Language features include a new "?." operator to perform inline null checks, and a new string interpolation feature is included to format strings inline.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic 2017 (code named VB "15.0") was released with Visual Studio 2017.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Extends support for new Visual Basic 15 language features with revision 2017, 15.3, 15.5, 15.8.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Introduces new refactorings that allow organizing source code with one action.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic 2019 (code named VB "16.0") was released with Visual Studio 2019.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] It is the first version of Visual Basic focused on .NET Core.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] A minor update was later released as Visual Basic 16.9 which only added the ability to consume init-only properties.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] This was done to maintain compatibility with C# 9.0 per the current development strategy of the language.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic 17.0 enables the System.Runtime.CompilerServices.CallerArgumentExpressionAttribute.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] Visual Basic 17.13 recognizes the unmanaged generic constraint and the System.Runtime.CompilerServices.OverloadResolutionPriorityAttribute for method resolution.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] The official Visual Basic compiler is written in Visual Basic and is available on GitHub as a part of the .NET Compiler Platform.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] MonoDevelop was an open-source alternative IDE.
[src:visual-basic-net/visual-basic-net] The Gambas environment is also similar but distinct from Visual Basic, as is the Visual FB Editor for FreeBasic.
